column5: In checking the Minnesota DOT website, it looks like both branches of I-35 through the Twin Cities are relatively construction free this year. Can anyone confirm that? We usually go 35W on the Minneapolis side because it seems a bit quicker IF there are no orange barrel slowdowns.
Take 35E....no construction this year that I know of. With 35W, there is always some sort of slow-down and a mess with 94 traffic merging, etc. Steve
What about the bridge in Lakeville?
